-- Syncrude Weakens After Suncor Reports Edmonton Refinery Work
-- B y   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 2012-03-08T22:04:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/syncrude-weakens-after-suncor-reports-edmonton-refinery-work.html
The discount for Syncrude oil from
 Canada  weakened after  Suncor Energy Inc. (SU)  reported work at its
Edmonton refinery in  Alberta .  Suncor is conducting “operational process work” at the
plant, according to a community hotline message late yesterday.
The refinery has a capacity of 134,900 barrels a day, according
to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Syncrude (USCSSYNS) ’s discount to U.S. benchmark West Texas
Intermediate widened $1 to $13.50 a barrel at 4:10 p.m. in  New
York , the largest gap since Feb. 21, according to data compiled
by Bloomberg.  Western Canada Select (USCSWCAS)  strengthened $1 to $35 below WTI. The
discount for Bakken oil widened $1 to $22 a barrel, the largest
gap since Feb. 10.  In the U.S. Gulf Coast,  Light Louisiana Sweet’s (USCSLLSS)  premium to
WTI widened 45 cents to $20.25 a barrel.  Heavy Louisiana Sweet (USCSHLSE) 
weakened 25 cents to a premium of $22.  Thunder Horse’s premium to WTI added 90 cents to $19.50 and
 Mars Blend (USCSMARS)  strengthened 75 cents to a premium of $15.30.
Poseidon’s premium added 70 cents to $14.75. Southern Green
Canyon’s gained 75 cents to $14.50 over WTI.  West Texas Sour (USCSWTSM) ’s discount narrowed 5 cents to $4.30 a
barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Aaron Clark  in New York at 
